{{Background|file=Smiler horde..jpg}}
<div style="background: #000000; border: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 0px; padding: 30px 20px; margin: 5px 10px; color: #FFFFFF; margin-bottom: 20px; overflow: hidden;">
'''Frowners''' are typically docile entities, that are similar to [[Entity 3|Smilers]]. They are recognizable for their signature reflective eyes and gleaming teeth and appear to be between is six to ten feet tall. They are speculated to be amorphous similar to Smilers.
[[File:Frownersillustration.webp|thumb|A drawing of a frowner.]]
If '''Frowners''' are provoked or seen as a threat, they will turn aggressive and exit their docile state. It is unknown whether a '''Frowner''' can re-enter their docile state once it exits it, so caution is advised when near them. The '''Frowners''' seem innately hostile to [[Entity 3|Smilers]] and will exit their docile state upon sensing their presence. '''Frowners''' possess a unique ability to convert [[Entity 3|Smilers]] into them by gouging out their eyes with their claws. '''Frowners''' are also known to have a sense of humor, although this may be exclusive to Level Frown. On rare occasions, '''Frowners''' have assisted wanderers to Level Frown. There also have been occasional reports of '''Frowners''' befriending wanderers that are perceived to have good moral values.
</div>
|padding=2rem 15%|number=1}}


In 2015, a discovery would by made by the [[Entity Research Committee]] about the true nature of the entities, when a mission to study Frowners by the group uncovered the truth that they were in fact anomalous fox-like entities, thus resulting in the revision of their documentation within the Database. Although renaming Frowners and moving the entities' article to a different number was discussed with the administrators of the Database via email, their current slot was allowed to remain for the time being due to most wanderers being familiar with their previous classification. 

